                                In addition, many functions such as the cargo tracking system, bargaining of goods prices, inventory management modules in the e-commerce infrastructure will make your work easier.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <h4 class="cizgi">3) Create a Category</h4>
                            </p>
                            <p>Another thing you need to sell clothes online is categories. When it comes to clothing, women's clothing, men's clothing and children's clothing come to mind. You can sell only one of these product groups, or you can sell all women's, men's and children's clothing. By creating these categories, you can add your products and start selling through your e-commerce site.</p>
                            <p>
                                <h4 class="cizgi">4) Pay Attention to Cargo Management</h4>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                One of the most problematic processes in online sales is the shipping process. Many customers complain about wrong shipping, downtime, shipping delay, etc. Returns to the cancellation and return process for reasons.
                                In order not to be adversely affected by these processes, please do the cargo management well and inform your customers at every stage after placing the order.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <h4 class="cizgi">5) Join Social Media</h4>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                After many answers to the question of how to sell clothes online, in this section of our article, we will discuss what you need to do to increase sales. The increase in the use of social media forces brands to participate in these platforms.
                            </p>
                            <p>Create your social media account to become one of the brands that convert potential customers into permanent customers and get ahead of your competitors with the content they share on social media platforms. Post regularly on these accounts to reassure your customers and get them to shop with you.</p>

                            <p>
                                <h4 class="cizgi">6) Organize Events</h4>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                One of the most effective ways to increase online clothing sales is to organize events. If you want to increase your clothing sales, you can create events on your e-commerce site and announce these events to your customers via social media.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <h4 class="cizgi">7) Build Your Mobile App</h4>
                            </p>
